name: Ipswich Public Library
directions: On the bottom floor next to the back door.
comment:
Accesible to wheelchairs or mobility aids, there's an elevator to get to it if you have a wheelchair (Level G2). There are two, gendered single stall bathrooms. Ask the staff if you have trouble finding them. 
Hours:
Thursday	9AM–5PM
Friday	9AM–5PM
Saturday	9AM–4PM
Sunday	1–4PM
Monday	9AM–8PM
Tuesday	9AM–8PM
Wednesday	9AM–8PM
Its closed Saturday and Sunday from memorial day to labor day.

name: Starbucks

name: Starbucks
directions: Its in the back of the restaurant. There are two restrooms and they are gender neutral, you will find them located in the back hall in doors on the right they are clearly labeled.

name: Damascus United Methodist Church
directions:
Top floor: through the sanctuary, all the way down the hall, turn right down hallway, on the left. To avoid the sanctuary (because a service or something is going on), go in the left entrance upstairs and go down the stairs, then follow bottom floor directions.
Bottom floor: there are a couple entrances to the bottom floor, but if you can find your way to the hallway with the "labyrinth" and go down that hallway towards the elevator, you turn right down the hallway and it's on the left. From the stairs described in the top floor directions specifically, just go straight down the hallway, through the door, and down the hallway to the right, then same directions as described earlier.
comment: It's for sure open between about 7:30 am and at least noon on Sundays, with services happening between 8:15 and about 9:15 and between 11:00 and about noon those mornings. The church does have a website you can check for other times it might be open (damascusumc.org).

name: Texas Tech University, Science Building (Physics/Geosciences)
directions: Bathroom is located on the first/basement floor, left wing, a little past halfway down the hall (just beyond the drinking fountain). An accessible entrance to the building is on the left exterior side, where an elevator may be used to get to the ground floor. If you use this left entrance, simply go straight from either the elevators or stairs - this is the left wing.
comment: No one should bother you - it's just students and faculty in the building and no one really gives anyone else a second glance.

name: Memorial College Center at Armstrong University

name: Oracle America Inc

comment: The office is employee only, but we have LGBTQ+ employees, I know of one transgendered and one non-binary person whom I've worked with here.  Figured it was worth putting on here, in case someone was looking for a job and wanted to see the bathroom situation.

name: Jeffrey's Bistro

name: Kroger Marketplace

name: The BottleHouse Brewing Company and Meadery

comment: The BottleHouse is a safe space for all members of the LGBTQIA+ community and has a single stall, all gender bathroom. If you feel unsafe, please inform staff and they will help.
